generated_description:  This painting, "Jacob Blessing the Children of Joseph," created by Rembrandt in 1656, reflects the Baroque period's emphasis on dramatic lighting and emotional intensity. The scene captures a moment of familial blessing, resonating with themes of family, faith, and divine favor prevalent during the 17th century. The Baroque style, characterized by its dynamic compositions and rich contrasts, underscores the emotional depth and narrative focus typical of the era.
retrieved_context: . 1661-1662) – Nationalmuseum, Stockholm. The majority of the original painting is now lost as Rembrandt cut it up in order for it to be sold. It is also his last secular history painting.
